<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" leftmargin="0" topmargin="0">
Erudites have long known the art of making strong tailored armors from the silks of the terrorantula and her offspring (the terrorantulings). Additionally, they have learned how to make 6 robes that are wearable by any INT casting class.<p>
As with all other cultural tradeskills, unless otherwise specified, these items must be made by someone of the proper race (Erudite) using their erudite sewing kit. Note that cultural tradeskill containers are not fooled by illusions.<p>
<p>With regards to the robes, spell research combines can be performed by any INT caster in their advanced spell research containers available in the Gulf of Gunthak. Ribbons can be made by any tailor. Dye components are foraged, as well as mob drops in the same zone in which the items can be foraged. The spell research items other than parchment and quill (vendor sold) are random mob drops off higher level mobs throughout the world.</p>
<p>Erudian robe patterns are obtained by erudites from Valani Gadriek (in Erudin at -1373, -250). Tell her "I want a robe pattern" to receive the no drop robe pattern. <font color="#800000"><i>Evil erudites take note that this vendor is near the zoneline with no other NPCs near her, so as long as you're able to get past the guards in Toxxulia Forest via invis or a bit of running, you'll be able to obtain your patterns from her with little problem.</i></font></p>
